List dataQuotes = [
  'The Prophet ﷺ said, "Whoever is patient, Allah will grant him patience, and no one is given a gift better and more comprehensive than patience." So when trials come your way, bear them with patience, for Allah rewards the patient abundantly. (Sahih al-Bukhari)',
  'The Prophet ﷺ said, "Amazing is the affair of the believer, for everything is good for him." If something good happens, he is grateful; if something bad happens, he is patient—and both are blessings. (Sahih Muslim)',
  'The Prophet ﷺ said, "Whoever puts his trust in Allah, He will suffice him." So place your worries in His hands, for He is the best provider and protector. (Sunan At-Tirmidhi)',
  'The Prophet ﷺ said, "Make things easy and do not make things difficult; give glad tidings and do not repel people." Let your character reflect kindness, mercy, and a welcoming spirit to others. (Sahih al-Bukhari & Muslim)',
  'The Prophet ﷺ said, "The most beloved deeds to Allah are those done consistently, even if small." So hold firm to your good actions, for sincerity and consistency are more valuable than grandeur. (Sahih al-Bukhari)',
];
